Package: metarep
Title: Replicability-Analysis Tools for Meta-Analysis
Version: 1.2.0
Depends: R (>= 4.1), meta (>= 6.0-0)
Suggests: metafor (>= 1.9.9), lme4, numDeriv, BiasedUrn, knitr,
        rmarkdown
Authors@R: person("Iman","Jaljuli", role=c("cre","aut"),
        email="jaljuli.iman@gmail.com")
Date: 2023-12-15
URL: https://github.com/IJaljuli/metarep
Description: User-friendly package for reporting replicability-analysis
        methods, affixed to meta-analyses summary. The
        replicability-analysis output provides an assessment of the
        investigated intervention, where it offers quantification of
        effect replicability and assessment of the consistency of
        findings. - Replicability-analysis for fixed-effects and
        random-effect meta analysis: - r(u)-value; - lower bounds on
        the number of studies with replicated positive and\or negative
        effect; - Allows detecting inconsistency of signals; - forest
        plots with the summary of replicability analysis results; -
        Allows Replicability-analysis with or without the common-effect
        assumption.
